title: Kraftwerk and the Electronic Revolution--- MarkStar
description:
Engaging and comprehensive, this documentary examines the deeply influential German "krautrock" band Kraftwerk, from their founding in 1970 to their bold, decades-long experimentation with electronic effects. Rare concert videos, interviews with band members, commentary by music authorities and other materials reveal how this landmark group's pivotal sound is reflected in electronica, synth-pop, techno and other musical styles.
